				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes. The problem is that the speed compensation inserts dummy frames in NTSC mode, i.e. once in six frames ppu_waitnmi waits two frames rather than one. In this extra frame split won't take effect, which will make the bottom part scroll into a wrong position for a frame.<br /><br />In current version automatic speed correction is disabled by default (could enabled in the crt0.s).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

